
SOURCE: https://venturebeat.com/2017/11/09/voice-recognition-and-machine-learning-make-service-bots-better/
AGENT: Peter Quinlan, Tata Communications
GOAL: Utilizing advancements in AI to implement 'robots with customer service skills'
DATA: The bot speaks to the customer in an accent they will understand based on their accent. This requires large datasets of accents. Similarly, the system knows all the customers past experience/communications with the company.
METHODS: The bot addresses the customers concerns using the collected wisdom of the company, including the absolute latest data on issues other customers face and how to solve them. Can provide solutions without errors. Follows up to make sure solution worked.
RESULTS: Potential to increase customer satisfaction and loyalty as well as making the customer service experience more seamless.
COMMENTS: None.
